<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Earning Merit</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Members accumulate merit through the participation of successful guild merit raids. Each raid or mobs within a raid earn points for members in attendance.<br>
<br>
A guild merit raid must satisfy the following requirements:<br>
<br>
Include at least 18 characters (exceptions may be made for epic encounters) <br>
Composed of at least 75% guild members <br>
Incorporate attainable goals that benefit the guild or its members<br>
No merit will be awarded for unsuccessful raids. No merit will be awarded to members who leave before the conclusion of the raid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Spending Merit</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Loot shall be awarded to members on the basis of total merit points and usability. Upon the availably of any loot item, members who can benefit from said item may request it. The member who has the highest number of merit points and can use the loot item will be awarded the loot item.<br>
<br>
A designated amount of merit points will be deducted from the member’s merit pool for each item awarded.<br>
<br>
Members are eligible to receive only major one loot item per raid, unless there are no requests for an item.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Loot Exceptions</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Quest pieces (e.g. tears from HoT drakes) may be awarded to the participant who is nearest to completion. <br>
Particular spells and items (e.g. Greater Remove Curse) that are of a tactical use for the guild may be awarded by the officers’ discretion based on the betterment of the guild. <br>
Components quest keys (e.g. Trak tooth for VP) may be awarded by the officers’ discretion based upon availability and classes needed for a successful raid. <br>
Epic components shall be awarded to the member who is nearest completion or banked until they are needed, unless the goal of the raid is to acquire specific component(s) for member(s).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Multiple Characters</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Merit is assigned to each member for each account that member operates.<br>
<br>
Raid capable characters on a single account share the same pool of merit points.<br>
<br>
Raid capable characters on multiple accounts that can participate simultaneously use separate merit pools. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/binfinitusvindicat>Infinite Vision</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm17>Guild Policies</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.infinitusvindicat.com">Infinite Vision Home</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font> <body bgcolor="#333366" text="#FFFFFF" topmargin="0" leftmargin="0" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0">

